messages.message: Just a quick check, I see that the provenance tracking on aihub-uat.internal.instabase.com (http://aihub-uat.internal.instabase.com) (15% fields with provenance, 0% right) is way worse then aihub.uat.instabase.com (http://aihub.uat.instabase.com) (90% provenance, 80% right), is that expected at the moment?
Can you share your docs and your field prompts and prompt types?

The documents are attached (Build for the configuration and Run for the "blind" test). The fields and prompts are all in dutch, happy to share them. Perhaps its best to first test it with just the bankstatements (0h699KoypPMGlcn35MrG.pdf & 8rMt0tXkseECLbtiuVM7.pdf)

No provenance tracking on Commercial (https://aihub-uat.internal.instabase.com/hub/apps/24a0f21a-50e0-4e89-8fbf-e8fc762625ab/batch/fb885720-fefa-4d11-b3af-b19feef5e530)

Provenance tracking on AI Hub (https://aihub.uat.instabase.com/hub/apps/8acf3b55-639c-4b7a-bdfd-ed95e563ce75/batch/bdc16050-cc02-4f88-ba6d-65f57054a338)
Third prompt is: Welke banktransacties betreffen inkomen uit uitzendwerk, antwoord met een tabel met kolommen boekdatum, omschrijving, bedrag
cc @Kathy Wu would you be the right person to look into this?
Maybe the passport might actually be a more easy example
